[3626.749796, "o", "                              document that  details  how  posix\u001b[m\r\n                              mode affects bash's behavior.\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mprivileged\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                              Same as \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mverbose\u001b[0m Same as \u001b[1m-v\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mvi\u001b[0m      Use  a vi-style command line edit‐\u001b[m\r\n                              ing interface.  This also  affects\u001b[m\r\n                              the  editing  interface  used  for\u001b[m\r\n                              \u001b[1mread\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-e\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mxtrace\u001b[0m  Same as \u001b[1m-x\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n                      If \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m is supplied with no \u001b[4moption-name\u001b[24m, the\u001b[m\r\n                      values of the current options are printed.\u001b[m\r\n                      If \u001b[1m+o\u001b[0m is supplied with no  \u001b[4moption-name\u001b[24m,  a\u001b[m\r\n                      series  of  \u001b[1mset\u001b[0m  commands  to recreate the\u001b[m\r\n                      current option settings  is  displayed  on\u001b[m\r\n     "]
[3626.749835, "o", "              "]
[3626.749877, "o", "   the standard output.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m      Turn  on  \u001b[4mprivileged\u001b[24m  mode.  In this mode,\u001b[m\r\n                      the \u001b[1m$ENV\u001b[0m and \u001b[1m$BASH_ENV\u001b[0m files are not  pro‐\u001b[m\r\n                      cessed,  shell functions are not inherited\u001b[m\r\n                      from the environment, and  the  \u001b[1mSHELLOPTS\u001b[0m,\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mBASHOPTS\u001b[0m,  \u001b[1mCDPATH\u001b[0m,  and  \u001b[1mGLOBIGNORE\u001b[0m  vari‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ables, if they appear in the  environment,\u001b[m\r\n                      are ignored.  If the shell is started with\u001b[m\r\n                      the effective user (group) id not equal to\u001b[m\r\n                      the  real  user (group) id, and the \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m op‐\u001b[m\r\n"]
[3626.750022, "o", "                      tion is not supplied,  these  actions  are\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6839 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.780998, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3626.781029, "o", "                      taken  and the effective user id is set to\u001b[m\r\n                      the real user id.  If  the  \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m  option  is\u001b[m\r\n                      supplied at startup, the effective user id\u001b[m\r\n                      is not reset.   Turning  this  option  off\u001b[m\r\n                      causes the effective user and group ids to\u001b[m\r\n                      be set to the real user and group ids.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-r\u001b[0m      Enable restricted shell mode.  This option\u001b[m\r\n                      cannot be unset once it has been set.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-t\u001b[0m      Exit  after reading and executing one com‐\u001b[m\r\n                      mand.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-u\u001b[0m      Treat unset variables and parameters other\u001b[m\r\n                      than  the  special parameters \"@\" and \"*\",\u001b[m\r\n                      or array variables subscripted with \"@\" or\u001b[m\r\n"]
[3626.781038, "o", "                      \"*\", as an error when performing parameter\u001b[m\r\n                      expansion.  If expansion is  attempted  on\u001b[m\r\n               "]
[3626.78117, "o", "       an  unset variable or parameter, the shell\u001b[m\r\n                      prints an error message, and, if  not  in‐\u001b[m\r\n                      teractive, exits with a non-zero status.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-v\u001b[0m      Print shell input lines as they are read.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-x\u001b[0m      After  expanding  each \u001b[4msimple\u001b[24m \u001b[4mcommand\u001b[24m, \u001b[1mfor\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      command, \u001b[1mcase\u001b[0m command, \u001b[1mselect\u001b[0m command,  or\u001b[m\r\n                      arithmetic  \u001b[1mfor\u001b[0m  command,  display the ex‐\u001b[m\r\n                      panded value of \u001b[1mPS4\u001b[0m, followed by the  com‐\u001b[m\r\n                      mand and its expanded arguments or associ‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ated word list.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-B\u001b[0m      The shell performs  brace  expansion  (see\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6865 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.811874, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3626.812029, "o", "                      \u001b[1mBrace\u001b[0m \u001b[1mExpansion\u001b[0m above).  This is on by de‐\u001b[m\r\n                      fault.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-C\u001b[0m      If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m does not overwrite an  exist‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ing  file with the \u001b[1m>\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m>&\u001b[0m, and \u001b[1m<>\u001b[0m redirect‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ion operators.   This  may  be  overridden\u001b[m\r\n                      when  creating  output  files by using the\u001b[m\r\n                      redirection operator \u001b[1m>|\u001b[0m instead of \u001b[1m>\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-E\u001b[0m      If set, any trap on \u001b[1mERR\u001b[0m  is  inherited  by\u001b[m\r\n                      shell  functions,  command  substitutions,\u001b[m\r\n                      and commands executed in a subshell  envi‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ronment.  The \u001b[1mERR\u001b[0m trap is normally not in‐\u001b[m\r\n                      herited in such cases.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-H\u001b[0m      Enable  \u001b[1m!\u001b[0m   style  history   substitution.\u001b[m\r\n                      This  option  is  on  by  default when the\u001b["]
[3626.812045, "o", "m\r\n                      shell is interactive.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-P\u001b[0m      If set, the shell does  not  resolve  sym‐\u001b[m\r\n                      bolic  links  when executing commands such\u001b[m\r\n                      as \u001b[1mcd\u001b[0m that change the current working  di‐\u001b[m\r\n                      rectory.   It  uses the physical directory\u001b[m\r\n                      structure instead.  By default, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m  fol‐\u001b[m\r\n                      lows the logical chain of directories when\u001b[m\r\n                      performing commands which change the  cur‐\u001b[m\r\n                      rent directory.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-T\u001b[0m      If  set, any traps on \u001b[1mDEBUG\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mRETURN\u001b[0m are\u001b[m\r\n                      inherited by shell functions, command sub‐\u001b[m\r\n                      stitutions,  and  commands  executed  in a\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6891 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.84247, "o", "\r\u001b[K                      subshell environment.  The \u001b[1mDEBUG\u001b[0m  and  \u001b[1mRE‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mTURN\u001b[0m  traps  are normally not inherited in\u001b[m\r\n                      such cases.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m--\u001b[0m      If no arguments follow this  option,  then\u001b[m\r\n                      the positional parameters are unset.  Oth‐\u001b[m\r\n                      erwise, the positional parameters are  set\u001b[m\r\n                      to  the  \u001b[4marg\u001b[24ms,  even if some of them begin\u001b[m\r\n                      with a \u001b[1m-\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n"]
[3626.842646, "o", "              \u001b[1m-\u001b[0m       Signal the end of options, cause  all  re‐\u001b[m\r\n                      maining  \u001b[4marg\u001b[24ms  to be assigned to the posi‐\u001b[m\r\n                      tional parameters.  The \u001b[1m-x\u001b[0m and \u001b[1m-v\u001b[0m  options\u001b[m\r\n                      are turned off.  If there are no \u001b[4marg\u001b[24ms, the\u001b[m\r\n                      positional parameters remain unchanged.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              The options are off by  default  unless  otherwise\u001b[m\r\n              noted.  Using + rather than - causes these options\u001b[m\r\n              to be turned off.  The options can also be  speci‐\u001b[m\r\n              fied  as  arguments to an invocation of the shell.\u001b[m\r\n              The current set of options may  be  found  in  \u001b[1m$-\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n              The return status is always true unless an invalid\u001b[m\r\n              option is encountered.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mshift\u001b[0m [\u001b[4mn\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n              The positional parameters from \u001b[4mn\u001b[24m+1 ... are renamed\u001b[m\r\n              to  \u001b[1m$1\u001b[0m \u001b[1m....\u001b[0m  Pa"]
[3626.84266, "o", "rameters represented by the numbers\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m$#\u001b[0m down to \u001b[1m$#\u001b[0m-\u001b[4mn\u001b[24m+1 are unset.  \u001b[4mn\u001b[24m must be a non-neg‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6917 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.873651, "o", "\r\u001b[K              ative number less than or equal to \u001b[1m$#\u001b[0m.  If \u001b[4mn\u001b[24m is 0,\u001b[m\r\n              no parameters are changed.  If \u001b[4mn\u001b[24m is not given,  it\u001b[m\r\n              is  assumed to be 1.  If \u001b[4mn\u001b[24m is greater than \u001b[1m$#\u001b[0m, the\u001b[m\r\n              positional parameters are not changed.  The return\u001b[m\r\n              status  is  greater than zero if \u001b[4mn\u001b[24m is greater than\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m$#\u001b[0m or less than zero; otherwise 0.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mshopt\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-pqsu\u001b[0m] [\u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m] [\u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m ...]\u001b[m\r\n              Toggle the values of settings controlling optional\u001b[m\r\n              shell  behavior.  The settings can be either those\u001b[m\r\n              listed below, or, if the \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m option is used,  those\u001b[m\r\n              available  with  the  \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m option to the \u001b[1mset\u001b[0m builtin\u001b[m\r\n              command.  With no options, or with the \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m  option,\u001b[m\r\n              a  list of all settable options is displayed, with\u001b[m\r\n              an indication of whe"]
[3626.873748, "o", "ther or not each  is  set;  if\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[4moptnames\u001b[24m are supplied, the output is restricted to\u001b[m\r\n              those options.  The \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m option causes output to  be\u001b[m\r\n              displayed  in  a form that may be reused as input.\u001b[m\r\n              Other options have the following meanings:\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-s\u001b[0m     Enable (set) each \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-u\u001b[0m     Disable (unset) each \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-q\u001b[0m     Suppresses normal output (quiet mode);  the\u001b[m\r\n                     return status indicates whether the \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n                     is set or unset.  If multiple \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m argu‐\u001b[m\r\n                     ments  are given with \u001b[1m-q\u001b[0m, the return status\u001b[m\r\n                     is zero if all \u001b[4moptnames\u001b[24m are  enabled;  non-\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6943 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.905344, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3626.905373, "o", "                     zero otherwise.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m     Restricts the values of \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m to be those\u001b[m\r\n                     defined  for  the  \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m  option  to  the  \u001b[1mset\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                     builtin.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              If  either  \u001b[1m-s\u001b[0m or \u001b[1m-u\u001b[0m is used with no \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m argu‐\u001b[m\r\n              ments, \u001b[1mshopt\u001b[0m shows only those  options  which  are\u001b[m\r\n              set  or  unset,  respectively.   Unless  otherwise\u001b[m\r\n              noted, the \u001b[1mshopt\u001b[0m options are disabled  (unset)  by\u001b[m\r\n              default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              The  return status when listing options is zero if\u001b[m\r\n              all  \u001b[4moptnames\u001b[24m  are  enabled,  non-zero  otherwise.\u001b[m\r\n              When setting or unsetting options, the return sta‐\u001b[m\r\n              tus is zero unless an \u001b[4moptname\u001b[24m is not a valid shell\u001b[m\r\n              option.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              The list of \u001b[1mshopt\u001b[0m options is:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1massoc_expand_onc"]
[3626.905381, "o", "e\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n         "]
[3626.905546, "o", "             If  set,  the  shell  suppresses  multiple\u001b[m\r\n                      evaluation of associative array subscripts\u001b[m\r\n                      during  arithmetic  expression evaluation,\u001b[m\r\n                      while executing builtins that can  perform\u001b[m\r\n                      variable  assignments, and while executing\u001b[m\r\n                      builtins that perform array dereferencing.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6969 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.936613, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3626.936786, "o", "              \u001b[1mautocd\u001b[0m  If set, a command name that is the name of\u001b[m\r\n                      a  directory is executed as if it were the\u001b[m\r\n                      argument to the \u001b[1mcd\u001b[0m command.   This  option\u001b[m\r\n                      is only used by interactive shells.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcdable_vars\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, an argument to the \u001b[1mcd\u001b[0m builtin com‐\u001b[m\r\n                      mand that is not a directory is assumed to\u001b[m\r\n                      be  the  name of a variable whose value is\u001b[m\r\n                      the directory to change to.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcdspell\u001b[0m If set, minor errors in the spelling of  a\u001b[m\r\n                      directory  component  in a \u001b[1mcd\u001b[0m command will\u001b[m\r\n                      be corrected.  The errors checked for  are\u001b[m\r\n                      transposed  characters,  a missing charac‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ter, and one character  too  many.   If  a\u001b[m\r\n                      correction  is  found, the corrected file‐\u001b"]
[3626.936883, "o", "[m\r\n                      name is printed, and the command proceeds.\u001b[m\r\n                      This  option  is  only used by interactive\u001b[m\r\n                      shells.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcheckhash\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m checks that a  command  found\u001b[m\r\n                      in  the hash table exists before trying to\u001b[m\r\n                      execute it.  If a hashed command no longer\u001b[m\r\n                      exists, a normal path search is performed.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcheckjobs\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set,  \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m  lists  the  status  of any\u001b[m\r\n                      stopped and running jobs before exiting an\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6995 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.968227, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3626.968263, "o", "                      interactive  shell.   If any jobs are run‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ning, this causes the exit to be  deferred\u001b[m\r\n                      until  a  second exit is attempted without\u001b[m\r\n                      an intervening command  (see  \u001b[1mJOB\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mCONTROL\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      above).   The shell always postpones exit‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ing if any jobs are stopped.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcheckwinsize\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m checks the window size  after\u001b[m\r\n                      each  external  (non-builtin) command and,\u001b[m\r\n                      if necessary, updates the values of  \u001b[1mLINES\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      and  \u001b[1mCOLUMNS\u001b[0m.   This  option is enabled by\u001b[m\r\n                      default.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcmdhist\u001b[0m If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m attempts to save all lines of\u001b[m\r\n                      a  multiple-line  command in the same his‐\u001b[m\r\n                      tory entry.  This allows  easy  re-editing\u001b[m\r\n     "]
[3626.968272, "o", "                 of  multi-line  commands.   This option is\u001b[m\r\n                      enabled by default, but only has an effect\u001b[m\r\n                      if  command  history  is  enabled,  as de‐\u001b[m\r\n                      scribed above under \u001b[1mHISTORY\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat31\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat32\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat40\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat41\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat42\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat43\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcompat44\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7021 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3626.999587, "o", "\r\u001b[K              \u001b[1mcompat50\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      These control aspects of the shell's  com‐\u001b[m\r\n                      patibility  mode  (see \u001b[1mSHELL\u001b[0m \u001b[1mCOMPATIBILITY\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mMODE\u001b[0m below).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mcomplete_fullquote\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m quotes all shell  metacharac‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ters in filenames and directory names when\u001b[m\r\n                      performing completion.  If not  set,  \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      removes  metacharacters such as the dollar\u001b[m\r\n                      sign from the set of characters that  will\u001b[m\r\n                      be  quoted  in  completed  filenames  when\u001b[m\r\n                      these metacharacters appear in shell vari‐\u001b[m\r\n                      able  references in words to be completed.\u001b[m\r\n"]
[3626.999617, "o", "                      This means that dollar signs  in  variable\u001b[m\r\n                      names  that expand to directories will not\u001b[m\r\n                      be quoted; however, any dollar  signs  ap‐\u001b[m\r\n                      pearing  in  filenames will not be quoted,\u001b[m\r\n                      either.  This is active only when bash  is\u001b[m\r\n                      using backslashes to quote completed file‐\u001b[m\r\n                      names.  This variable is set  by  default,\u001b[m\r\n                      which is the default bash behavior in ver‐\u001b[m\r\n                      sions through 4.2.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mdirexpand\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m replaces directory names with\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7047 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3627.031291, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3627.031321, "o", "                      the  results  of  word expansion when per‐\u001b[m\r\n                      forming filename completion.  This changes\u001b[m\r\n                      the  contents of the readline editing buf‐\u001b[m\r\n                      fer.  If not set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m  attempts  to  pre‐\u001b[m\r\n                      serve what the user typed.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mdirspell\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m attempts spelling correction\u001b[m\r\n                      on directory names during word  completion\u001b[m\r\n                      if  the  directory name initially supplied\u001b[m\r\n                      does not exist.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mdotglob\u001b[0m If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m includes filenames  beginning\u001b[m\r\n                      with  a `.' in the results of pathname ex‐\u001b[m\r\n                      pansion.  The filenames \u001b[1m``.''\u001b[0m  and  \u001b[1m``..''\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      must always be matched explicitly, even if\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mdotglob\u001b[0m is set.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              "]
[3627.03133, "o", "\u001b[1mexecfail\u001b[0m\u001b"]
[3627.031337, "o", "[m\r\n                      If set, a non-interactive shell  will  not\u001b[m\r\n                      exit  if it cannot execute the file speci‐\u001b[m\r\n                      fied as an argument to  the  \u001b[1mexec\u001b[0m  builtin\u001b[m\r\n                      command.   An  interactive  shell does not\u001b[m\r\n                      exit if \u001b[1mexec\u001b[0m fails.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mexpand_aliases\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7073 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3627.063484, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[3627.063516, "o", "                      If set, aliases are expanded as  described\u001b[m\r\n                      above  under  \u001b[1mALIASES\u001b[0m.  This option is en‐\u001b[m\r\n                      abled by default for interactive shells.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mextdebug\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set at shell invocation, or in a  shell\u001b[m\r\n                      startup  file,  arrange to execute the de‐\u001b[m\r\n                      bugger profile before  the  shell  starts,\u001b[m\r\n                      identical  to  the  \u001b[1m--debugger\u001b[0m option.  If\u001b[m\r\n                      set after  invocation,  behavior  intended\u001b[m\r\n                      for use by debuggers is enabled:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1m1.\u001b[0m     The   \u001b[1m-F\u001b[0m   option  to  the  \u001b[1mdeclare\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                             builtin displays  the  source  file\u001b[m\r\n                             name  and line number corresponding\u001b[m\r\n                             to each function name  supplied  as\u001b[m\r\n                             an argument.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r"]
[3627.063525, "o", "\n                      \u001b[1m2.\u001b[0m     If  the  command  run  by the \u001b[1mDEBUG\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                             trap returns a non-zero value,  the\u001b[m\r\n                             next command is skipped and not ex‐\u001b[m\r\n                             ecuted.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1m3.\u001b[0m     If the command  run  by  the  \u001b[1mDEBUG\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                             trap  returns a value of 2, and the\u001b[m\r\n                             shell is executing in a  subroutine\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7099 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3627.0941, "o", "\r\u001b[K                             (a shell function or a shell script\u001b[m\r\n                             executed  by  the   \u001b[1m.\u001b[0m   or   \u001b[1msource\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                             builtins),  the  shell  simulates a\u001b[m\r\n                             call to \u001b[1mreturn\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1m4.\u001b[0m     \u001b[1mBASH_ARGC\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mBASH_ARGV\u001b[0m are updated\u001b[m\r\n                             as  described in their descriptions\u001b[m\r\n                             above).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1m5.\u001b[0m     Function tracing is  enabled:  com‐\u001b[m\r\n                             mand substitution, shell functions,\u001b[m\r\n                             and subshells invoked with  \u001b[1m(\u001b[0m  \u001b[4mcom‐\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n                             \u001b[4mmand\u001b[24m \u001b[1m)\u001b[0m inherit the \u001b[1mDEBUG\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mRETURN\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                             traps.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1m6.\u001b[0m     Error tracing is  enabled:  command\u001b[m\r\n                             substitution,  shell functions, and\u001b[m"]
[3627.09413, "o", "\r\n                             subshells invoked with \u001b[1m(\u001b[0m \u001b[4mcommand\u001b[24m  \u001b[1m)\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                             inherit the \u001b[1mERR\u001b[0m trap.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mextglob\u001b[0m If set, the extended pattern matching fea‐\u001b[m\r\n                      tures described above under  \u001b[1mPathname\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mEx‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mpansion\u001b[0m are enabled.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mextquote\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, \u001b[1m$\u001b[0m'\u001b[4mstring\u001b[24m' and \u001b[1m$\u001b[0m\"\u001b[4mstring\u001b[24m\" quoting is\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7125 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3627.126069, "o", "\r\u001b[K                      performed within  \u001b[1m${\u001b[0m\u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m\u001b[1m}\u001b[0m  expansions\u001b[m\r\n                      enclosed in double quotes.  This option is\u001b[m\r\n                      enabled by default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mfailglob\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, patterns which fail to match file‐\u001b[m\r\n                      names  during pathname expansion result in\u001b[m\r\n                      an expansion error.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mforce_fignore\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, the suffixes specified by the \u001b[1mFIG‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mNORE\u001b[0m  shell variable cause words to be ig‐\u001b[m\r\n                      nored when performing word completion even\u001b[m\r\n                      if the ignored words are the only possible\u001b[m\r\n                      completions.  See  \u001b[1mSHELL\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mVARIABLES\u001b[0m  above\u001b[m\r\n                      for a description of \u001b[1mFIGNORE\u001b[0m.  This option\u001b[m\r\n                      is enabled by default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mglobasciir"]
[3627.126097, "o", "anges\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, range expressions used in  pattern\u001b[m\r\n                      matching  bracket expressions (see \u001b[1mPattern\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mMatching\u001b[0m above) behave as if in the tradi‐\u001b[m\r\n                      tional  C  locale  when performing compar‐\u001b[m\r\n                      isons.  That is, the current locale's col‐\u001b[m\r\n                      lating sequence is not taken into account,\u001b[m\r\n                      so \u001b[1mb\u001b[0m will not collate between \u001b[1mA\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mB\u001b[0m, and\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7151 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3627.157208, "o", "\r\u001b[K                      upper-case and lower-case ASCII characters\u001b[m\r\n                      will collate together.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mglobskipdots\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set,  pathname  expansion  will  never\u001b[m\r\n                      match  the  filenames  \u001b[1m``.''\u001b[0m   and \u001b[1m``..''\u001b[0m,\u001b[m\r\n                      even if the pattern begins with  a  \u001b[1m``.''\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n                      This option is enabled by default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mglobstar\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set, the pattern \u001b[1m**\u001b[0m used in a pathname\u001b[m\r\n                      expansion context will match all files and\u001b[m\r\n                      zero  or  more directories and subdirecto‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ries.  If the pattern is followed by a  \u001b[1m/\u001b[0m,\u001b[m\r\n                      only directories and subdirectories match.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mgnu_errfmt\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set,  shell error messages are written\u001b[m\r\n                      in the standard GNU error mess"]
[3627.157238, "o", "age format.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mhistappend\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, the history list  is  appended  to\u001b[m\r\n                      the  file  named by the value of the \u001b[1mHIST‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      \u001b[1mFILE\u001b[0m variable when the shell exits, rather\u001b[m\r\n                      than overwriting the file.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7177 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3627.188125, "o", "\r\u001b[K              \u001b[1mhistreedit\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, and \u001b[1mreadline\u001b[0m is being used, a user\u001b[m\r\n                      is given  the  opportunity  to  re-edit  a\u001b[m\r\n                      failed history substitution.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mhistverify\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set,  and  \u001b[1mreadline\u001b[0m is being used, the\u001b[m\r\n                      results of history  substitution  are  not\u001b[m\r\n"]
[3627.188332, "o", "                      immediately  passed  to  the shell parser.\u001b[m\r\n                      Instead, the resulting line is loaded into\u001b[m\r\n                      the \u001b[1mreadline\u001b[0m editing buffer, allowing fur‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ther modification.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mhostcomplete\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, and \u001b[1mreadline\u001b[0m is being  used,  \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      will  attempt  to perform hostname comple‐\u001b[m\r\n                      tion when a word containing a \u001b[1m@\u001b[0m  is  being\u001b[m\r\n                      completed  (see  \u001b[1mCompleting\u001b[0m under \u001b[1mREADLINE\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      above).  This is enabled by default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mhuponexit\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m will send \u001b[1mSIGHUP\u001b[0m to all  jobs\u001b[m\r\n                      when an interactive login shell exits.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1minherit_errexit\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set, command substitution inherits the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line "]
[3627.188435, "o", "7203 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
