[3627.220051, "o", "                      value of the \u001b[1merrexit\u001b[0m  option,  instead  of\u001b[m\r\n                      unsetting  it in the subshell environment.\u001b[m\r\n                      This option is enabled when \u001b[4mposix\u001b[24m \u001b[4mmode\u001b[24m  is\u001b[m\r\n                      enabled.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1minteractive_comments\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set,  allow a word beginning with \u001b[1m#\u001b[0m to\u001b[m\r\n                      cause that word and all remaining  charac‐\u001b[m\r\n                      ters  on that line to be ignored in an in‐\u001b[m\r\n                      teractive  shell  (see  \u001b[1mCOMMENTS\u001b[0m   above).\u001b[m\r\n                      This option is enabled by default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mlastpipe\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If set, and job control is not active, the\u001b[m\r\n                      shell runs the last command of a  pipeline\u001b[m\r\n                      not executed in the background in the cur‐\u001b[m\r\n                      rent shell environment.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mlithist\u001b[0m If set, and t"]
[3627.220062, "o", "he \u001b[1mcmdhist\u001b[0m option is enabled,\u001b[m\r\n                      multi-line  commands are saved to the his‐\u001b[m\r\n                      tory with embedded  newlines  rather  than\u001b[m\r\n                      using semicolon separators where possible.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mlocalvar_inherit\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                      If  set, local variables inherit the value\u001b[m\r\n                      and attributes of a variable of  the  same\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 7229 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
